<!DOCTYPE function SYSTEM "qtfmfunction.dtd">
<function name = "sqrt" overload = "true">
<short>Square root</short>
<syntax>Y = sqrt(X)</syntax>
<long>
<para>
<code>sqrt(X)</code> computes the square root of each element of the
quaternion array <code>X</code>.
</para>
<para>
The quaternion square root is easily defined in terms of the polar form:
<italic>q</italic> = |<italic>q</italic>|exp(μθ). Then √<italic>q</italic>
= √|<italic>q</italic>|exp(μθ/2).
</para>
</long>
<examples>
<precode>
>> sqrt(qi)
 
ans = 0.7071 + 0.7071 * I + 0 * J + 0 * K
 
>> ans.^2
 
ans = 0 + 1 * I + 0 * J + 0 * K
</precode>
</examples>
<seealso>
<matlabfun name = "sqrt"/>
</seealso>
</function>

